summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23749, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of California Avenue, from West Graham Street to Lowman Drive, all in The City of Seattle, by grading and curbing the same, all in accordance with Majority Petition, being File No. 39717, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle," approved on the 1st day of April, A. D. 1910.
